<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow">
<title>Dxfferent — Proposal for Optara</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600;0,9..40,700;1,9..40,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
@font-face {
  font-family: 'PPMonument';
  src: url('https://dxfferent.com/wp-content/themes/interly-child/fonts/PPMonumentExtended-Black.woff2') format('woff2'),
       url('https://dxfferent.com/wp-content/themes/interly-child/fonts/PPMonumentExtended-Black.woff') format('woff');
  font-weight: 900;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

*, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

:root {
  --bg: #0a0a0a;
  --frame: #0f0f0f;
  --alt: #141414;
  --accent: #ED4C35;
  --success: #49C481;
  --gold: #c8a040;
  --card-light: #f8f7f5;
  --text: #e0e0e0;
  --text-dim: #888;
  --text-dark: #1a1a1a;
  --border: #222;
  --mono: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
  --body: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  --display: 'PPMonument', 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
}

html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

body {
  font-family: var(--body);
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
  line-height: 1.7;
  font-size: 16px;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}

.document-frame {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 40px auto;
  background: var(--frame);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 2px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.band { padding: 64px 56px; }
.band-alt { background: var(--alt); }

.header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 24px 56px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 16px;
}
.header-logo img { height: 28px; display: block; }
.header-ref {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

h2 {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 28px;
  font-weight: 900;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
  line-height: 1.2;
}
h3 {
  font-family: var(--body);
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}
.mono-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}
p { margin-bottom: 16px; color: var(--text); }
p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

.hero h2 {
  font-size: 36px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.hero-sub {
  font-size: 18px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  max-width: 640px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.cover-letter p { font-size: 15px; }
.cover-letter .salutation {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.bullet-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 24px 0;
}
.bullet-list li {
  padding: 10px 0 10px 24px;
  position: relative;
  font-size: 15px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
}
.bullet-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.bullet-list li::before {
  content: '\2014';
  color: var(--accent);
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  font-weight: 700;
}
.sign-off {
  margin-top: 28px;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}
.sign-off strong {
  display: block;
  font-style: normal;
  color: #fff;
  margin-top: 4px;
}

.stats-row {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 20px;
}
.stat-card {
  background: var(--alt);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 20px 16px;
  text-align: center;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}
.stat-number {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: var(--accent);
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.stat-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}

.challenge-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 20px;
}
.challenge-card {
  background: var(--card-light);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 28px 24px;
  color: var(--text-dark);
}
.challenge-card h3 {
  color: var(--text-dark);
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.challenge-card p {
  color: #444;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

.approach-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }
.step {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
  gap: 20px;
  align-items: start;
}
.step-num {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 28px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: var(--accent);
  line-height: 1;
  padding-top: 4px;
}
.step-title {
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
}
.badge-done {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  background: var(--success);
  color: #fff;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.step-body p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-dim); margin: 0; }

.roadmap-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
  font-size: 14px;
}
.roadmap-table th {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  text-align: left;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.roadmap-table td {
  padding: 14px 16px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
  vertical-align: top;
}
.roadmap-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
.roadmap-table .sprint-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--accent);
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.roadmap-table .focus-label { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; }

.callout-box {
  background: rgba(237, 76, 53, 0.06);
  border: 1px solid rgba(237, 76, 53, 0.25);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 28px 24px;
}
.callout-box strong { color: #fff; }
.callout-box p { font-size: 15px; margin: 0; }

/* Single pricing card - centered */
.pricing-single {
  max-width: 480px;
  margin: 0 auto 32px;
}
.pricing-card {
  border: 1px solid var(--gold);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--gold);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 36px 28px;
  position: relative;
  background: var(--alt);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}
.pricing-badge {
  position: absolute;
  top: -12px;
  right: 20px;
  background: var(--gold);
  color: #fff;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 4px 14px;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
.pricing-name {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 16px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: #fff;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.pricing-tagline {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.pricing-amount {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 36px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.pricing-period {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 28px;
}
.pricing-features {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
  flex: 1;
}
.pricing-features li {
  padding: 8px 0;
  font-size: 14px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: start;
  gap: 10px;
}
.pricing-features li::before {
  content: '\2713';
  color: var(--success);
  font-weight: 700;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 1px;
}
.btn-select {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 14px;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  text-align: center;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.2s;
  background: var(--accent);
  color: #fff;
}
.btn-select:hover { background: #d9432d; }

.onetime-box {
  background: var(--alt);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 28px 24px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.onetime-row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 8px 0;
  font-size: 15px;
}
.onetime-row.total {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  margin-top: 8px;
  padding-top: 16px;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 18px;
  color: #fff;
}
.validity {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  text-align: center;
}

.qa-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 28px; }
.qa-q {
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
  font-size: 16px;
}
.qa-a { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-dim); margin: 0; }

.terms-box {
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 32px 28px;
}
.terms-box h2 { font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.terms-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  counter-reset: term;
}
.terms-list li {
  padding: 10px 0;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.terms-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

.footer {
  padding: 20px 56px;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  text-align: center;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  line-height: 1.8;
}

/* ---- PAGE 2 ---- */
.back-link {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  text-decoration: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: color 0.2s;
}
.back-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }

.step-banner {
  background: var(--accent);
  padding: 14px 56px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}
.step-banner-title {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: #fff;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
}
.step-banner-steps {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}
.step-banner-steps .current { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .step-banner { padding: 12px 24px; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; text-align: center; }
}

.selection-card {
  background: var(--alt);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 32px 28px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 16px;
}
.selection-service {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: #fff;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
.selection-price {
  font-family: var(--display);
  font-size: 28px;
  font-weight: 900;
  color: var(--accent);
}

.philosophy-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin-top: 20px;
}
.philosophy-list li {
  padding: 10px 0 10px 24px;
  position: relative;
  font-size: 15px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
}
.philosophy-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.philosophy-list li::before {
  content: '\2014';
  color: var(--accent);
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  font-weight: 700;
}

.included-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
}
.included-list li {
  padding: 12px 0;
  font-size: 15px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: start;
  gap: 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
}
.included-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.included-list li::before {
  content: '\2713';
  color: var(--success);
  font-weight: 700;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  font-size: 16px;
  margin-top: 1px;
}

.sprint-recap {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  counter-reset: sprint;
}
.sprint-recap li {
  counter-increment: sprint;
  padding: 12px 0 12px 40px;
  position: relative;
  font-size: 15px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
}
.sprint-recap li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.sprint-recap li::before {
  content: counter(sprint) '.';
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--accent);
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
}

.form-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 20px;
}
.form-group {
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.form-group label {
  display: block;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.form-group input[type="text"],
.form-group input[type="email"] {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 4px;
  color: #fff;
  font-family: var(--body);
  font-size: 15px;
  transition: border-color 0.2s;
}
.form-group input:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: var(--accent);
}
.form-group input::placeholder { color: #555; }

.checkbox-group {
  display: flex;
  align-items: start;
  gap: 12px;
  margin: 28px 0;
}
.checkbox-group input[type="checkbox"] {
  width: 18px;
  height: 18px;
  margin-top: 2px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  accent-color: var(--accent);
  cursor: pointer;
}
.checkbox-group label {
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  cursor: pointer;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.btn-submit {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 16px;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  text-align: center;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: not-allowed;
  transition: all 0.2s;
  background: #333;
  color: #666;
}
.btn-submit.enabled {
  background: var(--accent);
  color: #fff;
  cursor: pointer;
}
.btn-submit.enabled:hover { background: #d9432d; }
.form-note {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 16px;
}

.signature-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 40px;
  margin-top: 40px;
}
.sig-col h3 {
  font-size: 16px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.sig-field { margin-bottom: 20px; }
.sig-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.sig-value {
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #fff;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
  min-height: 28px;
}
.sig-blank {
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  min-height: 28px;
}

.success-message {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 48px 24px;
}
.success-icon {
  width: 64px;
  height: 64px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--success);
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  font-size: 28px;
  color: #fff;
}
.success-message h2 {
  font-family: var(--display);
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}
.success-message p {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
  max-width: 480px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.hidden { display: none !important; }

@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .document-frame { margin: 0; border: none; border-radius: 0; }
  .band { padding: 40px 24px; }
  .header { padding: 16px 24px; }
  .footer { padding: 16px 24px; }
  h2 { font-size: 22px; }
  .hero h2 { font-size: 26px; }
  .stats-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .challenge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .pricing-single { max-width: 100%; }
  .signature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
  .selection-card { flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
  .step { grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .form-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .roadmap-table { font-size: 12px; }
  .roadmap-table th, .roadmap-table td { padding: 10px 8px; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ==================== PAGE 1: THE QUOTE ==================== -->
<div id="page-quote">
<div class="document-frame">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-logo">
      <img src="https://dxfferent.com/wp-content/themes/interly-child/images/logo.svg" alt="Dxfferent">
    </div>
    <div class="header-ref">REF 2026-043 &middot; 2026-04-30 &middot; NET 14</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 1: Hero -->
  <div class="band hero">
    <div class="mono-label">Prepared For</div>
    <h2>Optara</h2>
    <p class="hero-sub">A complete IT Glue reimplementation to turn your documentation platform into a structured, scalable foundation for automation and growth.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 2: Cover Letter -->
  <div class="band band-alt cover-letter">
    <p class="salutation">Dear Joel,</p>
    <p>Thank you for the open conversation during our deep dive session. You were clear about the situation: IT Glue is not working the way it should, other tools that depend on it are pulling data incorrectly, and your team does not have time to figure out how to fix it. We understand that completely.</p>
    <p>After reviewing your IT Glue environment, Melissa confirmed what you described: the platform needs a full reimplementation. Integrations are not pulling correctly, asset types and site summaries are not structured for how your business operates, and there is no consistent documentation architecture. The good news is that the fix is not switching platforms. It is rebuilding what you have so it actually works for you.</p>
    <p>What we are proposing is straightforward: we come in, rebuild your IT Glue from the ground up, and hand it back to you in a state where your team trusts the data, your integrations work, and the platform is ready for the automations you want to build on top of it.</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>We start with a one-time implementation project to rebuild the foundation.</li>
      <li>After go-live, we continue with monthly guidance to keep the system healthy, train new hires, and expand into automation.</li>
      <li>We work in bi-weekly sprints with clear deliverables per sprint.</li>
      <li>In addition to our sessions, we are available for all relevant questions over Teams chat.</li>
      <li>We have a shared responsibility: we guide and advise on best practices, your team handles the day-to-day data entry and adoption.</li>
      <li>We are a sparring partner for all MSP-related topics, not just IT Glue.</li>
      <li>We can normally start within one month after quote approval.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If there are any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us.</p>
    <p class="sign-off">Kind regards,<strong>Max de Kwaasteniet</strong></p>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 3: Stats -->
  <div class="band">
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <span class="stat-number">150+</span>
        <span class="stat-label">MSP Implementations</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <span class="stat-number">2-WEEK</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Sprint Cadence</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <span class="stat-number">3-PHASE</span>
        <span class="stat-label">Programme</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 4: Discovery Findings -->
  <div class="band band-alt">
    <h2>What We Found</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px">During our review of your IT Glue environment, we identified several areas that need attention. These are common challenges we see in MSPs that have set up IT Glue but never fully implemented it.</p>
    <div class="challenge-grid">
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>Integrations Pulling Incorrectly</h3>
        <p>Tools that depend on IT Glue are not getting the right data. Lifecycle cannot identify hardware refresh and warranty opportunities because configurations are not structured correctly. Other integrations have the same problem: bad data in, bad data out.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>Assets &amp; Configurations</h3>
        <p>Asset types are not structured for how your business operates. The question "are we using assets the right way?" applies across the board: configurations, flexible assets, and how data is categorized.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>Site Summaries &amp; Topologies</h3>
        <p>Site summaries and network topologies are not set up to give your team the quick overview they need per client. These are the first things a technician should see when opening a customer record.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>Documentation Spread Across Systems</h3>
        <p>Critical information lives in IT Glue, SharePoint, Teams, and other places. Without a clear decision on what goes where, your team wastes time searching and still does not trust what they find.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>SOPs &amp; Checklists</h3>
        <p>IT Glue has built-in SOPs and checklists, but they are not being used. Standard procedures live in people's heads instead of being documented and linked to the right assets and organizations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card">
        <h3>AI &amp; Automation Readiness</h3>
        <p>The end goal is running AI and automations on top of IT Glue data: employee onboarding, role changes, standard procedures. That requires clean, structured, and consistently formatted data as the foundation. The current state does not support it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 4b: Business Impact -->
  <div class="band">
    <h2>What This Can Do For Your Business</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:24px">The technical work is necessary, but what matters is what it can unlock. Based on what we have seen across 25+ IT Glue implementations, these are the areas where MSPs typically see the biggest returns.</p>

    <div class="challenge-grid">
      <div class="challenge-card" style="border-left-color:var(--success)">
        <h3>Lifecycle &amp; Dependent Tools</h3>
        <p>Lifecycle depends on accurate configuration data in IT Glue. When that data is structured correctly, it can surface hardware refresh opportunities, warranty expirations, and end-of-life alerts that would otherwise go unnoticed. The same applies to other tools in your stack that pull from IT Glue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card" style="border-left-color:var(--success)">
        <h3>Return On Existing Investments</h3>
        <p>You are already paying for IT Glue, Lifecycle, and a range of integrations. When the underlying data is unreliable, those tools cannot deliver their full value. This project does not add tools. It is designed to make the tools you already own work the way they should.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card" style="border-left-color:var(--success)">
        <h3>Technician Efficiency</h3>
        <p>When documentation lives in one trusted place instead of spread across IT Glue, SharePoint, and Teams, technicians typically spend less time searching and more time resolving. A clean single source of truth can significantly reduce the "let me ask someone" bottleneck.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="challenge-card" style="border-left-color:var(--success)">
        <h3>Automation &amp; AI Readiness</h3>
        <p>With clean, structured, and consistently formatted data, you create the foundation to run AI across your documentation and build automations for repeatable workflows like onboarding, role changes, and standard procedures. That potential is only available when the data underneath supports it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout-box" style="margin-top:24px;border-left-color:var(--success)">
      <p><strong>In short:</strong> You told us the biggest enemy is time, and that you would rather pay someone than have your team spend 40 or 80 hours trying to figure this out. That is what this project is designed to do. We bring the experience from 25+ IT Glue implementations, rebuild the platform, and hand it back in a state where your team can trust the data and your business tools can rely on it.</p>
    </div>

    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:16px;text-align:center;">Our lead consultant has completed 25+ IT Glue implementations across MSPs of varying sizes. References available on request.</p>

    <div style="margin-top:32px;padding-top:24px;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)">
      <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#555;text-align:center;margin-bottom:16px">Selected clients our consultants have worked with</p>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:36px;flex-wrap:wrap;opacity:0.5">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Cubics" style="height:28px;filter:brightness(0) invert(1)">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="IT Synergy" style="height:28px;filter:brightness(0) invert(1)">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Refa ICT" style="height:28px;filter:brightness(0) invert(1)">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="ICT&CO" style="height:28px;filter:brightness(0) invert(1)">
        <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Aspect ICT" style="height:28px;filter:brightness(0) invert(1)">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 5: Our Approach -->
  <div class="band">
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <div class="approach-steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">Review <span class="badge-done">Done</span></div>
          <p>We reviewed your IT Glue environment and identified the gaps. Based on that review, we have a clear picture of the current state and what needs to change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">Kick-off</div>
          <p>Once the quote is approved, we host a kick-off with your project team. We go into the goals, define the documentation architecture, and align on the sprint plan.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">Implementation</div>
          <p>We work through the reimplementation in bi-weekly sprints. Each sprint has a clear focus area: integrations, templates, data cleanup, or documentation structure. Every sprint we review and course-correct.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">04</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">Go-live</div>
          <p>We decide on the go-live date together. Before go-live we validate everything end-to-end. Training sessions for your team to make sure everyone knows the new way of working.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">05</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">Optimize &amp; Automate</div>
          <p>After go-live, we continue with monthly guidance. This is where the real value compounds: building automations on top of the clean data, expanding documentation coverage, and training new hires on the system.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 6: Programme -->
  <div class="band band-alt">
    <h2>Programme</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px">We work in a phased approach. The exact scope and timeline will be determined together during kick-off with our lead consultant. How fast we move depends on your team's capacity and the complexity of your environment.</p>
    <table class="roadmap-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Phase</th>
          <th>Focus</th>
          <th>What We Cover</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="sprint-label">Phase 1</td>
          <td class="focus-label">Foundation</td>
          <td>We activate and configure all relevant integrations so information flows into IT Glue automatically. We go through every Flexible Asset Template and determine per template which fields are needed and which are not, so your team captures exactly the right information. We establish the full documentation architecture: what you document in IT Glue, what lives elsewhere, naming conventions, and at what level of detail. Everything is set up to be scalable and structured from the start.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="sprint-label">Phase 2</td>
          <td class="focus-label">Build &amp; Clean</td>
          <td>We roll out the new structure across your client base. Outdated configurations get flagged and cleaned. Documentation templates get applied per organization. We work through the data quality backlog systematically, prioritizing active clients first. Your team starts working in the new structure under our guidance.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="sprint-label">Phase 3</td>
          <td class="focus-label">Adoption &amp; Automation</td>
          <td>With the foundation in place, we focus on adoption and expansion. SOPs and runbooks get centralized in IT Glue. We identify opportunities for automation: onboarding flows, role changes, standard procedures. Training sessions bring the full team up to speed. The platform becomes the single source of truth it was designed to be.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="callout-box">
      <p><strong>Why this matters:</strong> When IT Glue is properly structured and consistently maintained, everything downstream changes. Technicians find answers faster. New hires ramp up in days instead of weeks. And because the data is clean and structured, you can run AI across it and build automations on top of it: employee onboarding, role changes, standard procedures, offboarding. Those workflows that currently eat hours of your team's time can be standardized and automated. That is where the real operational leverage sits.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Band 7: Pricing -->
  <div class="band">
    <h2>Investment</h2>
    <div class="onetime-box">
      <div class="onetime-row">
        <span>IT Glue Reimplementation Project</span>
