  <!-- Band 8: Q&A -->
  <div class="band band-alt">
    <h2>Questions &amp; Answers</h2>
    <div class="qa-list">
      <div class="qa-item">
        <div class="qa-q">How long does the reimplementation take?</div>
        <p class="qa-a">This depends on the size of your client base and your team's capacity. Most reimplementations take between 3 and 6 months. We determine the pace together during kick-off.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-item">
        <div class="qa-q">Do you configure everything for us?</div>
        <p class="qa-a">We design the architecture, build the templates, and configure the integrations. Your team handles the client-specific data entry. We guide and advise throughout, but you own the knowledge.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-item">
        <div class="qa-q">What if we already have data in IT Glue?</div>
        <p class="qa-a">We work with what is there. Clean data gets migrated into the new structure. Outdated data gets flagged for review. We do not delete anything without your approval.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-item">
        <div class="qa-q">What happens after the implementation project?</div>
        <p class="qa-a">Guide as a Service continues with monthly guidance: optimization, automation, training, and ongoing support. The initial GaaS term is 3 months, then it renews monthly until written cancellation with a one-month notice period.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-item">
